<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-11-17T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-11-17T08:00:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6704:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Leopoldville</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Mallon</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leopoldville</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-11-17T14:00:00+01:00">November 17, 1940—2 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I have been asked to accompany High Commissioner de Larminat on a
                                visit by plane to Libreville and Port Gentil to witness the effects
                                of the recent bombs. Departure set for early in the morning November
                                20. Respectfully request Department’s advice in time to accept or
                                decline.</p>
                            <p>De Gaulle left for London today.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mallon</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>